<h2>Font Migration
</h2>

<p>The NSW Design System is rebranding and changing its typeface from <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Montserrat">Montserrat</a>
  to <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Public+Sans">Public Sans</a>.</p>

<p>To use Public Sans, switch your existing imports</p>

<p>HTML</p>

{{#>_docs-example hidden="true" open="true" code="language-html"}}
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Public+Sans:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
{{/_docs-example}}

<p>CSS</p>

{{#>_docs-example hidden="true" open="true" code="language-css"}}
  url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Public+Sans:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&amp;display=swap');
{{/_docs-example}}

<p>Make sure to upgrade to 2.14.X or later</p>

{{#>_docs-example hidden="true" open="true" code="language-bash"}}
  npm install nsw-design-system@2.14.X
{{/_docs-example}}

<p>In your <code>theme.scss</code>
  file, update the <code>--nsw-font-family</code>
  custom property</p>
{{#>_docs-example hidden="true" open="true" code="language-bash"}}
  --nsw-font-family: 'Public Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
{{/_docs-example}}

<p>If youâ€™re importing with the compiled CSS,
  make sure you to add <code>--nsw-font-family</code>
  custom property AFTER the import.</p>

{{#>_docs-example hidden="true" open="true" code="language-scss"}}
  @import 'node_modules/nsw-design-system/dist/css/main';

  :root {
  --nsw-font-family: 'Public Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
  }
{{/_docs-example}}

<p>If your are using JSDelivr, upgrade to
  version 2.14.0 and update the <code>--nsw-font-family</code>
  custom property:</p>

{{#>_docs-example hidden="true" open="true" code="language-html"}}
  <html>
  <head>
    ...
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/nsw-design-system@2.14.0/dist/css/main.css">
  </head>
  <style>
    :root {
      --nsw-font-family: 'Public Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
    }
  </style>
{{/_docs-example}}
